description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for Health Care Support Worker to join our busy Outreach Outpatient Departments covering Wetherby, Ripon, Alwoodley and Yeadon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will need to be a dynamic, flexible and highly motivated person with a professional attitude to join the Outpatient Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duties of this role will include, assisting practitioners with examinations, acting as a chaperone, undertaking clerical duties and liaising with various departments and clinicians.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates will need to have strong communication skills and to be able to work as part of a team. We are looking for individuals who are highly organised with experience of working in a clincial setting. An induction programme will be provided within the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Matron Issie Macniven on Issie.macniven@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Issie Macniven Job title: Matron Email address: Issie.macniven@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
